This paper is about the learning of neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the machine learning subfield of computer science. Specifically, it deals with the improper learning of multi-layer neural networks using an $\ell_1$ regularization method. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the application of the algorithm to computer vision (cs.CV) and the sample and time complexity of the method, which could be relevant to the subfield of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
